23/01/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski discussed army reforms Wednesday (22 January) with his Croatian counterpart, Zeljka Antunovic. 
The two officials agreed to share experiences in the field and vowed to hold more meetings, to better prepare the two armies in their bids for NATO membership. 
Buckovski will visit Kosovo early next month. 
(MIA, Makfax, A1 TV- 22/01/03)
